{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876891862,"sessionID":"ses_2857d4d9bffeHG1zGSwGfUb4w1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a82e010001zbKLNuNXH62Upk","messageID":"msg_d7a82d50f001MmwSCINxLVNNFP","sessionID":"ses_2857d4d9bffeHG1zGSwGfUb4w1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7c329b3aef214cab9609a289","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.github/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.github/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions — Technical Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Attribute | Value |\n6: |-----------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `.github` |\n8: | **Language** | YAML (GitHub Actions) |\n9: | **Size** | L (12 workflows) |\n10: | **Stage** | ST-1 completed (Implementation ready) |\n11: | **Reference** | `ci-cd/design.md` (workflows reference) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### 1. Workflow Organization\n18: \n19: ```\n20: .github/workflows/\n21: ├── main.yml                    # Docker build on PR\n22: ├── lint.yml                    # Go lint (golangci-lint)\n23: ├── codegen-check.yml           # Code generation drift check\n24: ├── test-coverage.yml           # Go test with coverage\n25: ├── e2e.yml                     # End-to-end tests on Kind\n26: ├── python-sdk-tests.yml        # Python SDK unit tests\n27: ├── python-lint.yml             # Python Ruff linting\n28: ├── codespell.yml               # Spelling verification\n29: ├── copyright-check.yml         # Copyright header enforcement\n30: ├── build-push-release.yml      # Release image publishing\n31: ├── dify-plugin-publish.yml    # Dify plugin release automation\n32: └── workflows-approve.yml       # First-time contributor approval\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### 2. Trigger Architecture\n36: \n37: | Trigger Type | Branches/Tags | Purpose |\n38: |--------------|---------------|---------|\n39: | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | PR validation |\n40: | `push` | `main`, `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | Main build + release tags |\n41: | `push` | `dify-plugin/v*` | Plugin publishing |\n42: | `merge_group` | — | Merge queue validation |\n43: | `workflow_call` | — | Reusable workflow invocation |\n44: | `pull_request_target` | `main`, `release-**` | Contributor approval |\n45: | `workflow_dispatch` | — | Manual trigger (future) |\n46: \n47: ### 3. Path Filter Strategy\n48: \n49: Uses `dorny/paths-filter` v2 for efficient conditional execution:\n50: \n51: | Filter Name | Patterns | Workflows |\n52: |-------------|----------|-----------|\n53: | `lint` | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml` | lint.yml |\n54: | `codegen` | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | codegen-check.yml |\n55: | `coverage` | `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**` | test-coverage.yml |\n56: | `copyright` | All except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | copyright-check.yml |\n57: | `python` | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml` | python-lint.yml |\n58: | `sdk` | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests.yml |\n59: \n60: ### 4. Runner Matrix\n61: \n62: | Language | Version | Workflows |\n63: |----------|---------|-----------|\n64: | Go | 1.24 | lint.yml, test-coverage.yml |\n65: | Go | 1.24.4 | codegen-check.yml, build-push-release.yml |\n66: | Go | 1.23 | e2e.yml |\n67: | Python | 3.12 | python-sdk-tests.yml |\n68: | Python | 3.10 | python-lint.yml |\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Data Structures\n73: \n74: ### 1. Workflow Metadata\n75: \n76: ```yaml\n77: # Example: Workflow structure template\n78: name: <workflow-name>\n79: on:\n80:   pull_request:\n81:     branches: [main, 'release-*']\n82:   push:\n83:     branches: [main]\n84: \n85: concurrency:\n86:   group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n87:   cancel-in-progress: true\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### 2. Job Configuration\n91: \n92: ```yaml\n93: jobs:\n94:   <job-name>:\n95:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n96:     steps:\n97:       - name: Checkout\n98:         uses: actions/checkout@v4\n99:       \n100:       - name: Path Filter\n101:         if: <conditional>\n102:         uses: dorny/paths-filter@v2\n103:         id: filter\n104:         with:\n105:           filters: |\n106:             <filter-name>:\n107:               - '<pattern>'\n108:       \n109:       - name: Run Action\n110:         if: steps.filter.outputs.<filter-name> == 'true'\n111:         run: |\n112:           <command>\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### 3. Environment Variables\n116: \n117: | Variable | Scope | Description |\n118: |----------|-------|-------------|\n119: | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | E2E workflow | Log collection directory |\n120: | `TAG` | Release workflow | Image tag (from git ref) |\n121: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | Release workflow | Container registry URL |\n122: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | E2E test | Workload Manager endpoint |\n123: | `ROUTER_URL` | E2E test | Router endpoint |\n124: | `API_TOKEN` | E2E test | Kubernetes service account token |\n125: \n126: ### 4. Secrets\n127: \n128: | Secret | Workflows | Purpose |\n129: |--------|-----------|---------|\n130: | `GITHUB_TOKEN` | build-push-release, workflows-approve | GHCR login, API operations |\n131: | `CODECOV_TOKEN` | test-coverage | Coverage upload (optional) |\n132: | `GH_TOKEN` | dify-plugin-publish | Cross-repo PR creation |\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## API Contracts\n137: \n138: ### 1. Workflow Dispatch Inputs\n139: \n140: ```yaml\n141: # Future: Manual workflow trigger\n142: on:\n143:   workflow_dispatch:\n144:     inputs:\n145:       test-suite:\n146:         type: choice\n147:         options: [unit, integration, e2e]\n148:         required: true\n149:       go-version:\n150:         type: string\n151:         default: '1.24'\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### 2. Workflow Call Inputs/Outputs\n155: \n156: ```yaml\n157: # test-coverage.yml reusable workflow\n158: on:\n159:   workflow_call:\n160:     inputs:\n161:       go-version:\n162:         type: string\n163:         default: '1.24'\n164:     secrets:\n165:       codecov-token:\n166:         required: false\n167:     outputs:\n168:       coverage-passed:\n169:         description: \"Whether coverage threshold met\"\n170:         value: ${{ jobs.coverage.outputs.coverage-passed }}\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### 3. Job Outputs\n174: \n175: ```yaml\n176: jobs:\n177:   coverage:\n178:     outputs:\n179:       coverage-passed: ${{ steps.coverage-check.outputs.passed }}\n180:     steps:\n181:       - id: coverage-check\n182:         run: |\n183:           PASSED=$((${{ steps.coverage.outputs.coverage }} >= 80))\n184:           echo \"passed=$PASSED\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## Error Handling\n190: \n191: ### 1. Step-Level Error Handling\n192: \n193: ```yaml\n194: - name: Build Docker image\n195:   run: make docker-build\n196:   continue-on-error: false  # Fail workflow on error\n197: \n198: - name: Optional coverage upload\n199:   if: success() && steps.codecov.outputs.token\n200:   run: codecov/upload-action@...\n201: ```\n202: \n203: ### 2. Job-Level Failure Handling\n204: \n205: ```yaml\n206: - name: Collect logs on failure\n207:   if: failure()\n208:   run: |\n209:     ./scripts/collect-logs.sh\n210:   \n211: - name: Cleanup always\n212:   if: always()\n213:   run: make e2e-clean\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### 3. Retry and Timeout\n217: \n218: ```yaml\n219: - name: Unstable test\n220:   uses: nick-fields/retry@v3\n221:   with:\n222:     timeout_minutes: 10\n223:     max_attempts: 3\n224:     command: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### 4. Error Conditions\n228: \n229: | Condition | Handling | Workflow |\n230: |-----------|----------|----------|\n231: | Docker build failure | Fail fast | main.yml |\n232: | Lint errors | Fail with output | lint.yml |\n233: | Coverage below threshold | Warn only (optional) | test-coverage.yml |\n234: | E2E test failure | Upload artifacts, fail | e2e.yml |\n235: | Codegen drift | Fail with diff | codegen-check.yml |\n236: | Kind cluster creation | Fail with logs | e2e.yml |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Testing Strategy\n241: \n242: ### 1. Workflow Validation\n243: \n244: #### Syntax Validation\n245: ```bash\n246: # Validate workflow YAML syntax\n247: actionlint .github/workflows/*.yml\n248: \n249: # Alternative: yamllint\n250: yamllint -c .yamllint .github/workflows/\n251: ```\n252: \n253: #### Dry-Run Testing\n254: ```bash\n255: # Use act (GitHub Actions local runner) for testing\n256: act -l  # List workflows\n257: act -n  # Dry-run\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ### 2. Path Filter Testing\n261: \n262: ```bash\n263: # Verify path filters match expected files\n264: # Test: Modify a Go file, verify lint.yml triggers but python-lint.yml doesn't\n265: git checkout main\n266: echo \"// test\" >> pkg/test.go\n267: git diff --name-only  # Should show pkg/test.go\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ### 3. Integration Testing\n271: \n272: | Test | Method | Verification |\n273: |------|--------|--------------|\n274: | Docker build | Run main.yml locally | Image created |\n275: | Lint check | Run on modified code | Lint errors detected |\n276: | E2E on Kind | Execute e2e.yml | Cluster created, tests pass |\n277: | Path filter | Modify filtered paths | Correct workflow triggers |\n278: | Release build | Tag push simulation | Images pushed to GHCR |\n279: \n280: ### 4. Test Coverage for Workflows\n281: \n282: ```yaml\n283: # Example: Workflow that tests other workflows\n284: name: Workflow Integration Test\n285: on:\n286:   pull_request:\n287:     paths:\n288:       - '.github/workflows/**'\n289: \n290: jobs:\n291:   validate-workflows:\n292:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n293:     steps:\n294:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n295:       - name: Validate YAML\n296:         run: |\n297:           for f in .github/workflows/*.yml; do\n298:             python3 -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('$f'))\" || exit 1\n299:           done\n300:       - name: Check action versions\n301:         run: |\n302:           grep -h 'uses:' .github/workflows/*.yml | sort -u\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Implementation Checklist\n308: \n309: ### Phase 1: Core Workflows\n310: - [ ] `main.yml` — Docker build verification\n311: - [ ] `lint.yml` — Go lint with path filter\n312: \n313: ### Phase 2: Testing Workflows\n314: - [ ] `test-coverage.yml` — Go coverage with codecov\n315: - [ ] `e2e.yml` — Kind cluster E2E tests\n316: - [ ] `codegen-check.yml` — Code generation verification\n317: \n318: ### Phase 3: Python Workflows\n319: - [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` — Python SDK tests\n320: - [ ] `python-lint.yml` — Python Ruff linting\n321: \n322: ### Phase 4: Quality Workflows\n323: - [ ] `codespell.yml` — Spelling checks\n324: - [ ] `copyright-check.yml` — Header enforcement\n325: \n326: ### Phase 5: Release Workflows\n327: - [ ] `build-push-release.yml` — Image publishing\n328: - [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` — Plugin release\n329: - [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` — Contributor approval\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## Dependencies\n334: \n335: | Action | Version | Purpose |\n336: |--------|---------|---------|\n337: | `actions/checkout` | v4 | Repository checkout |\n338: | `actions/setup-go` | v5 | Go environment |\n339: | `actions/setup-python` | v5 | Python environment |\n340: | `docker/setup-buildx-action` | v3 | Docker buildx |\n341: | `docker/login-action` | v3 | GHCR login |\n342: | `dorny/paths-filter` | v2 | Path-based filtering |\n343: | `helm/kind-action` | v1 | Kind cluster |\n344: | `codecov/codecov-action` | v4 | Coverage upload |\n345: | `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` | v4 | AWS (future) |\n346: \n347: ---\n348: \n349: ## Security Considerations\n350: \n351: 1. **Secret Management**: Use GitHub Secrets for all sensitive data\n352: 2. **Token Scoping**: Use minimal token scopes for workflow permissions\n353: 3. **Path Filtering**: Prevent unnecessary workflow runs\n354: 4. **Concurrency**: Cancel in-progress runs on new pushes\n355: 5. **Artifact Handling**: Clean up artifacts after retention period\n356: 6. **External Actions**: Pin to specific versions (SHA preferred)\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## References\n361: \n362: - Proposal: `proposal.md` (AR-034)\n363: - Specification: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n364: - Workflow Reference: `ci-cd/design.md`\n365: - Makefile: `Makefile` (build targets)\n366: - E2E Setup: `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n\n(End of file - total 366 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions — Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| **Module** | `.github` |\n| **Language** | YAML (GitHub Actions) |\n| **Size** | L (12 workflows) |\n| **Stage** | ST-1 completed (Implementation ready) |\n| **Reference** | `ci-cd/design.md` (workflows reference) |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 1. Workflow Organization\n\n```\n.github/workflows/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.github/design.md","time":{"start":1775876891838,"end":1775876891860}}}}
